in the server we have to find a file with following specs

owned by user bandit7
owned by group bandit6
33 bytes in size

so it wants me to use find command with owner , group and size filter that too on whole server - find /. -user bandit7 -group bandit6 -size 33c
find /. means to search whole server 
but the problem with this was that there were too many error messages so we can use 
2>/dev/null  this keeps the output clean and easy to read

final cmd - find /. -user bandit7 -group bandit6 -size 33c 2>/dev/null
this returned us a path to the file with specified features 
then use cat to read the file - cat ./var/lib/dpkg/info/bandit7.password

